doc.previous: The NC-4 was dismantled in Plymouth, and then loaded onto the USS Aroostook, the base ship for the Curtiss NC's transatlantic flight, [11] for the return journey to the United States. Aroostook arriving in New York Harbor on 2 July 1919.[12]
doc.after: Following the return of all three of the aircrews on board the ocean liner USS Zeppelin, a goodwill tour of the East Coast of the United States and the Gulf Coast of the Southern States was carried out by the aircrewmen.[3]
